aboutMe.en-US:
Juka is an upcoming rapid prototyping programming language.
It's meant to be fast, efficient, and cross-platform.

* __Builtin IDE:__ Juka has a simple built-in editor. Forget command prompts and terminals! Just focus on writing your sentences.
* __Multithreaded:__ Don't worry about complicated stuff like multithreading and multiprocessing. Juka automatically creates a thread whenever it needs to!
* __Single Repo:__ Create programs, share them with community! Help each other out. Juka is very community driven, so we are making sharing simple by introducing package manager.
* __Crossplatform:__ Run on Windows, Macintosh, or any other platform. We are building Juka on top of .NET CORE platform. If you can install .NET Core Runtime, then you can run the language.
* __Interface with other languages:__ We are building new ways to interact with Juka. Soon you will be able to import "compiled" code from other languages and use it in your program making it simple for non-coders to interact with your applications.
* __Free and Open Source:__ You might have heard that there is no such thing as free lunch. Well, Juka is 100% free and is an open source product. Forever. We just ask that you participate in our community and tell your friends about it by tweeting, facebooking, emailing or whatever the means.

faqs.en-US:
__Q: Does Juka work on Linux? __

A: *Juka is built on top of .NET Standard Library. This means that it can run on Windows, Linux, and Macintosh natively. We also support mobile platforms such as Android, iOS (iPhone and iPads), and Windows Phone. We also have plans to build programs for XBOX.*


__Q: What is Juka good for?__

A: *Juka is good for fast prototyping programs that run on almost any device.*


__Q: Could this language help me in college?__

A: *It could!*

description.en-US:
Join our ever growing Juka community. We use "Slack" for managing the community as it provides an easy way to stay connected. In order to join the community, you will need to be invited to our slack channel. You can receive an automatic invitation via email by filling out this form: [Slack Invitation Form](https://join.slack.com/t/jukalang/shared_invite/enQtNDgxMjA2Njc2ODAxLTE1NGE5MGVhYTlkNDg0Mzc3Zjc3ZDMxNTZiOWJiNTgyZmM3NjMyOGJmMTM4NmI5OGRhODJlOTQwOTFmZDY2Mzk)
If you already have an account, go to our slack channel located at: [https://jukalang.slack.com](https://jukalang.slack.com)

Juka is built by the community, for the community. Please consider contributing to the Juka GitHub repository at [https://github.com/jukaLang](https://github.com/jukaLang)
When you create new features, please follow the guidelines specified in the project documentation.
Need help? Don't want to read boring tutorial? Watch tutorial videos through YouTube at [Juka YouTube Channel](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCRkKqD0fnuVAJLJe9p4ZiKQ)
